            "definition": "Dyrosauroidea is the largest clade within Crocodylomorpha containing Dyrosaurus phosphaticus (Thomas 1893) but not Terminonaris robusta (Mook 1934), Pholidosaurus schaumburgensis von Meyer 1841, Pholidosaurus purbeckensis (Mansel-Pleydell 1888), Thalattosuchus superciliosus (Blainville 1853) or Anteopthalmosuchus hooleyi Salisbury and Naish 2011.",
